 According to a permit that they obtained from the City of Mbombela Local Municipality, they have the right to protest at every show. ALSO READ: Mpumalanga Show shines with joy “The circus is one of the that has interactions with wild animals. It’s a moral belief, if you don’t like it, you don’t like it. People need to understand that we all have different moral beliefs.”  He added that “just because the animals are in the circus it does not mean that they are being abused. I know that we look after our animals and I know that they are comfortable here and I that they are taken care of and that they know nothing else but my circus”.